# =============================================================================
# Whinfell_BUILD_Cousins - Strong .gitignore (per BEST_PRACTICES.md)
# =============================================================================
# Goal: Prevent accidental commits of large CSVs, raw data, archives, etc.
# Always use targeted `git add` (never `git add -A`).

# --- OS / Editor / Python ---
*.DS_Store
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.so
.Python
*.swp
*~
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Large data / generated artifacts (MUST stay out of git) ---
staged_raw/
Archive/
quarantine/
repo_cleanup*/
data/execution/
_desk_preview_out/

# --- Project-specific junk ---
NEXTFOUR.md.txt
08_Deliverables/Whinfell_Transmission_Map_Team_Memo_v1.1.md

# =============================================================================
# Selective whitelisting for whinfell_pipeline (legacy from phased development)
# We ignore the directory broadly then explicitly allow the files we want tracked.
# Only edit this section if you understand the impact on tracked files.
# =============================================================================

whinfell_pipeline/*

